.Data
.align 4
.equ MAX_DIGITS, 32768      @ constant for max digits
@oAddend1: .skip 131076      @ oAddend1 = memory for 32769 ints(int,int[32678])
@oAddend2: .skip 131076      @ oAddend2 init memory

/**************************************************************************
    (ARM FUNCTION A32)
    Assign the sum of oAddend1 and oAddend2 to oSum.  Return 0 (FALSE)
    if an overflow occurred, and 1 (TRUE) otherwise.

    int BigInt_add(BigInt_T oAddend1, BigInt_T oAddend2, BigInt_T oSum)
    r4 -> UiCarry
    r5 -> uiSum
    r6 -> i
    r7 -> isumLength
    r8 -> oAddend1
    r9 -> oAddend2
    r10-> oSum

    r0 -> oAddend1
    r1 -> oAddend2
    r2 -> oSum
    r3 -> iSumLegth
    r7 -> UiCarry
    r5 -> UiSum
    r6 -> i
    Return FALSE if overflow(0)
    OR
    Return TRUE if !overflow(1)
 **************************************************************************/

BigInt_add:
    @ push registers onto the stack (keep 8 byte allinged as per AAPCS)
    STMFD sp!, {r3,r4,r5,r6,r8,r9,lr}
    LDR r4, [r1]                @ r4 = oAddend2->iLenght2
    LDR r3, [r0]                @ r3 = oAddend1->iLength1
    MOV r9, r2			@ save r2 into r9
    CMP r4,r3                   @ Check which number is longer
    IT GE
    MOVGE r3,r4                 @ r3 = iSumLegth
    MOV r6, r3                  @ i = iSumLegth (the count)
    MOV r4, #0                  @ r4 = 0(UiCarry)
loop:
    LDR r8,[r0, #4]!     	@ r8 = oAddend1->auiDigits[i]
    LDR lr,[r1, #4]!     	@ r10 = oAddend2->auiDigits[i]
    ADD r5,r4,r8                @ Uisum += oAddend1->auiDigits[i]+UiCarry

    CMP r5,r8                   @ compare uisum to oAddend1->auiDigits[i]
    ITE LO
    MOVLO r4,#1                 @ uiCarry = 1 if lower(unsigned)
    MOVHS r4,#0			@ uiCarry = 0 if higher(signed)

    ADDS lr,r5,lr		@ Uisum += oAddend2->auiDigits[i]
    IT HS
    MOVHS r4,#1			@ uiCarry = 1 if lower(unsigned)LS
    STR lr,[r2, #4]!    	@ store into oSum->auiDigits[i] uiSum
    SUBS r6,r6,#1		@ Decrement i
    bne loop
end:
    LDR r5, =1                  @ Load r4 with 1(to be used in next store)
    LDR r1, =MAX_DIGITS         @ r1 = MAX_DIGITS
    CMP r4, r5                  @ check if uiCarry = 1
    BNE true

    CMP r3, r1                  @ check if OVERFLOW
    ITT EQ
    MOVEQ r0, #0                @ set return to 0(false)
    @ pop registers before branching out of func
    POPEQ {r3,r4,r5,r6,r8,r9,pc}
    add r2, r9, r3, asl #2
    ADD r3,r3, r5               @ iSumLength ++(r5 = 1)
    STR r5,[r2,# 4]             @ Osum->auiDigits[isumLength] = 1

true:
    STR r3, [r9]                @ Store iSumLenght -> oSum->iLength
    MOV r0, r5                  @ set return to 1(true)
    @ pop registers & brach back to fib.c
    LDMFD sp!, {r3,r4,r5,r6,r8,r9,pc}
@Global Functions
    .global BigInt_add
    .type BigInt_add, %function
@ Labels to access data
@addr_oAddend1 : .word oAddend1
@addr_oAddend2 : .word oAddend2
@addr_oSum : .word oSum
# make clean - removes all .o and executable files
# Select Compiler
CC = gcc

# compiler flags:
CFLAGS = -D NDEBUG -O3

# All the source Files
SRCS = fib.c bigint.c bigintaddOpt.c

# ALL object source files from SRCS
OBJS = $(SRCS:.c=.o)

# dependencies from objs
-include $(OBJS:.o=.d)

# command makes makefile ignore any 
# files named clean 
.PHONY: clean

# executable file
EXEC = fib

ALL: $(EXEC)
#link files
$(EXEC): $(OBJS)
		$(CC) $(CFLAGS) -o $(EXEC) $(OBJS)
#Compile Files
.c.o:
		$(CC) $(CFLAGS) -c $< -o $@
		$(CC) -MM $(CFLAGS) *.c > $*.d
#Delete .o and exec files
clean:
		$(RM) *.o *~ $(EXEC)
